==English==

===Etymology===
One who paints stripes on candy canes so as to cheer people up. The term arose in the 50's when volunteer hospital workers wore outfits with candy stripes

===Noun Phrase===
'''candy striper'''
#A volunteer worker in a hospital
#One who cheers others up with their exuberance
#:''The entire convalescent home came to life as soon as the '''candy striper''' Cindy arrived.''